-- -- Identifying Solar PV from Aerial Imagery Laurence Watson
Digimap GeoForum, March 2020
@LaurenceWWatson Co-founder at treebeard.io Locating solar panels is useful for better production forecasts, understanding load on the low-voltage electricity grid, and tracking solar growth across the world. In the UK, despite the Feed In Tariff database, many panel locations are not known. I used computer vision and machine learning techniques combined with overhead aerial imagery to find and locate UK solar panels and you can too.
